# Materials (read-only reference)

Path: `materials/` at repo root. Index: `docs/reference/materials-index.md`.

## Rules

1. **Do not edit** files under `materials/` unless the user explicitly asks to change a prototype or reference project.
2. **Do not** copy large chunks into `docs/llm-wiki/wiki/` as product truth. Production behavior lives in `apps/` and `packages/`.
3. **Consult on request** — when the user asks about UI/UX from designs, Figma exports, or assessment demos, read the relevant `materials/` subtree and cite paths.
4. **Wiki updates** — if a design decision is adopted in production code, update `docs/llm-wiki/wiki/` from **code**, not from materials alone. Optional: note in wiki that a screen was inspired by `materials/...` with a link.
5. **No auto-ingest** — do not run full LLM Wiki ingest on `materials/` without user direction.

## vs docs/llm-wiki

| Location | Agent may write? | Purpose |
|----------|------------------|---------|
| `docs/llm-wiki/wiki/` | Yes (per llm-wiki rules) | Compiled product/domain knowledge |
| `docs/llm-wiki/raw/` | No (human adds sources) | Immutable notes you ingest |
| `materials/` | No (unless asked) | Prototypes & design references |
